# Workflow State

- For numbered pipeline work, read `workflow-state.yaml` through `goodworkflows-state-manager` before acting.
- Only `goodworkflows-state-manager` writes `workflow-state.yaml`.
- Record stages, artifacts, decisions, blockers, verification, and git metadata when work spans multiple surfaces.
- Do not delete append-only history entries from decisions, issues, verification, or commits.
- If state and code disagree, record drift; do not hide it.
